1
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:36,692
[KONORI]
Honestly.

2
00:00:36,775 --> 00:00:39,858
That's not a simple
favor you're asking for.

3
00:00:39,942 --> 00:00:41,733
I know, and I'm sorry, Konori.

4
00:00:43,108 --> 00:00:44,900
But with only what I have
here in the hospital,

5
00:00:44,983 --> 00:00:48,858
it's not exactly easy to perform
all of my Judgment duties.

6
00:00:48,942 --> 00:00:50,067
[KONORI]
Sheesh.

7
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:52,067
Your wounds aren't even
completely healed yet.

8
00:00:52,150 --> 00:00:54,150
And wow, they look painful!

9
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,608
Hey! Maybe don't use your
clairvoyance ability

10
00:00:56,692 --> 00:00:59,817
in a hospital?
It's a little inappropriate!

11
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:03,483
[KONORI chuckles]
Still, I'm serious.

12
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:05,692
Don't push yourself too hard.

13
00:01:05,775 --> 00:01:07,692
Uiharu is worried about you.

14
00:01:08,775 --> 00:01:10,108
[KUROKO]
Yeah.

15
00:01:10,192 --> 00:01:12,650
She must feel partially
responsible for me getting hurt.

16
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:16,733
Since she led me into the
situation that resulted'

17
00:01:16,817 --> 00:01:18,150
in these injuries.

18
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:20,483
Probably.

19
00:01:20,567 --> 00:01:22,692
[KUROKO] But her blaming herself
is the reason I have to

20
00:01:22,775 --> 00:01:25,275
get better as soon as possible.

21
00:01:25,358 --> 00:01:26,650
You know her.

22
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:29,025
She'll feel like she has
to make up for this somehow.

23
00:01:31,317 --> 00:01:32,608
That's for sure.

24
00:01:32,692 --> 00:01:34,733
Reminds me of someone I know.

25
00:01:34,817 --> 00:01:35,817
What was that?

26
00:01:37,317 --> 00:01:38,275
[KONORI]
Nothing.

27
00:01:40,442 --> 00:01:41,900
[F MEMBER A]
Well, we did it!

28
00:01:41,983 --> 00:01:43,150
[M MEMBER A]
Finally.

29
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:45,025
[M MEMBER B]
Thank goodness.

30
00:01:45,108 --> 00:01:48,317
[M CHAIRMAN A]
Yes. You've done well, everyone.

31
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,025
But...

32
00:01:50,108 --> 00:01:52,858
Why do I have an awfully
bad feeling about this?

33
00:01:57,150 --> 00:02:00,775
[F REPORTER A] The Daihasei
Festival is about to begin!

34
00:02:00,858 --> 00:02:02,525
It's one of the few
times Academy City

35
00:02:02,608 --> 00:02:05,025
opens its doors
to the outside world,

36
00:02:05,108 --> 00:02:06,775
and parents of
the competing students,

37
00:02:06,858 --> 00:02:08,400
as well as many
other spectators,

38
00:02:08,483 --> 00:02:11,108
have gathered in the
main stadium to watch.

39
00:02:11,192 --> 00:02:12,567
[KOMOE]
Ms. Watanabe!

40
00:02:14,275 --> 00:02:16,483
Long time no see!

41
00:02:16,567 --> 00:02:19,317
Another year,
another festival, huh?

42
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,233
Ms. Tsukuyomi.

43
00:02:21,317 --> 00:02:23,858
May I ask why you're
dressed like that?

44
00:02:23,942 --> 00:02:25,108
[laughs]

45
00:02:25,192 --> 00:02:27,942
Someone has to cheer
on the students!

46
00:02:28,025 --> 00:02:29,983
Well, at least you're
supporting the children.

47
00:02:33,108 --> 00:02:34,567
[KOMOE]
That's right, I almost forgot.

48
00:02:34,650 --> 00:02:36,608
Shokuho is taking the
athlete's pledge this year,

49
00:02:36,692 --> 00:02:38,025
isn't she?

50
00:02:38,108 --> 00:02:39,233
[WATANABE]
Yes.

51
00:02:39,317 --> 00:02:41,192
The plan was to have
some Level 5s perform

52
00:02:41,275 --> 00:02:44,692
a sort of demonstration
this year.

53
00:02:44,775 --> 00:02:46,192
However...

54
00:02:47,858 --> 00:02:50,192
[SHOKUHO, SOGIITA]
The athlete's pledge!

55
00:02:50,275 --> 00:02:51,067
We will...

56
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:52,400
We all shall...

57
00:02:52,483 --> 00:02:54,483
[SOGIITA] ...adhere to the
ideals of sportsmanship

58
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:56,983
throughout this year's
Daihasei Festival.

59
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:59,483
[SHOKUHO] ...use our youthful
dreams and fervent wills

60
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:00,858
as our strength.

61
00:03:00,942 --> 00:03:03,275
And forge undying bonds with...

62
00:03:03,358 --> 00:03:05,025
Bonds with, uh...

63
00:03:05,108 --> 00:03:07,442
Man, what was it again?

64
00:03:07,525 --> 00:03:08,650
Ah, whatever!

65
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:10,150
We're gonna do something
or other with those

66
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:12,775
"undying bonds"
and our overflowing guts!

67
00:03:12,858 --> 00:03:13,900
[CROWD gasps]

68
00:03:13,983 --> 00:03:16,567
[SHOKUHO, SOGIITA
overlapping chatter]

69
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:24,150
[SOGIITA] ...be sure this
event creates fantastic,

70
00:03:24,233 --> 00:03:25,650
gutsy memories!

71
00:03:25,733 --> 00:03:28,942
And for any difficulties,
hardships, obstacles, trials,

72
00:03:29,025 --> 00:03:31,733
or tribulations that dare
stand in our way,

73
00:03:31,817 --> 00:03:34,233
we pledge to overcome
it all with guts!

74
00:03:35,692 --> 00:03:36,858
[CROWD cheers]

75
00:03:36,942 --> 00:03:38,608
[MIKOTO]
What was that?

76
00:03:38,692 --> 00:03:41,067
Well, that was basically
a disaster, wasn't it?

77
00:03:41,150 --> 00:03:42,108
Uh-huh.

78
00:03:43,275 --> 00:03:44,317
[F ANNOUNCER A]
Um...

79
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,442
This concludes our
opening ceremonies.

80
00:03:48,358 --> 00:03:49,733
[SHOKUHO]
He upstaged me.

81
00:05:22,317 --> 00:05:23,817
[SATEN]
The Daihasei Festival.

82
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:26,608
An event spanning seven days
that is held in Academy City

83
00:05:26,692 --> 00:05:28,483
every year.

84
00:05:28,567 --> 00:05:31,733
It's kind of like a
large-scale field day.

85
00:05:31,817 --> 00:05:33,775
Unlike conventional
athletic festivals,

86
00:05:33,858 --> 00:05:36,817
the Daihasei Festival has all
of Academy City's students

87
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,900
compete for their schools.

88
00:05:38,983 --> 00:05:40,442
Plus,

89
00:05:40,525 --> 00:05:43,358
TV stations broadcast what's
happening to the whole world!

90
00:05:43,442 --> 00:05:46,067
But the biggest difference...

91
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:50,233
...is that every single event
has espers competing in them!

92
00:05:50,317 --> 00:05:51,692
And you know what?

93
00:05:51,775 --> 00:05:54,192
They say that when espers
compete against each other,

94
00:05:54,275 --> 00:05:56,775
the resulting phenomenon
is one you won't ever find

95
00:05:56,858 --> 00:05:57,858
anywhere else!

96
00:05:57,942 --> 00:05:58,983
[UIHARU]
Hm?

97
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,775
Do you mean that
urban legend about

98
00:06:00,858 --> 00:06:02,608
whatever-it's-called metal?

99
00:06:02,692 --> 00:06:03,942
[SATEN]
Come on!

100
00:06:04,025 --> 00:06:06,358
Its name is "shadow metal."
It's not that hard.

101
00:06:06,442 --> 00:06:08,108
When dozens,
or better yet, hundreds

102
00:06:08,192 --> 00:06:09,733
of esper abilities clash,

103
00:06:09,817 --> 00:06:12,358
they say this mysterious
metal that's never been found

104
00:06:12,442 --> 00:06:14,900
naturally occurring
on Earth is created!

105
00:06:14,983 --> 00:06:16,900
And where else but
the Daihasei Festival

106
00:06:16,983 --> 00:06:18,608
could that possibly happen?

107
00:06:18,692 --> 00:06:20,483
Not only that, but it's so
rare that it goes for

108
00:06:20,567 --> 00:06:23,442
an astronomical price
if you find the right buyer.

109
00:06:23,525 --> 00:06:25,192
So we gotta look for it
while we have--

110
00:06:25,275 --> 00:06:27,900
[KUROKO]
Saten!

111
00:06:30,525 --> 00:06:34,733
[KUROKO] You still believe
in such ridiculous rumors?!

112
00:06:34,817 --> 00:06:36,567
What? Oh, not at all.

113
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:38,317
I was just messing around.

114
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,692
It's just a rumor!

115
00:06:39,775 --> 00:06:43,067
I know not to take it seriously.

116
00:06:43,150 --> 00:06:44,483
[KUROKO] That's what you
said last time, and look

117
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:45,692
what happened!

118
00:06:45,775 --> 00:06:47,317
There's nothing wrong
with being curious,

119
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,483
but maybe consider
the consequences!

120
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:50,942
[SATEN]
Whoa!

121
00:06:51,025 --> 00:06:53,317
Misaka's in her gym uniform
up on that giant monitor!

122
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,483
Sissy? Where?

123
00:06:55,858 --> 00:06:57,817
[RADIO DJ]
And in Lane Four, this pair!

124
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:03,150
From Tokiwadai Middle School,
Mikoto Misaka and Mitsuko Kongo!

125
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:05,775
That's the lineup for the
third event of block seven,

126
00:07:05,858 --> 00:07:07,150
the three-legged race!

127
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:09,692
Now it's time to
explain the rules!

128
00:07:09,775 --> 00:07:11,525
[KUMOKAWA] If the band around
their ankles comes off,

129
00:07:11,608 --> 00:07:13,150
they are disqualified.

130
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:15,692
Use of their abilities to
directly harm other competitors

131
00:07:15,775 --> 00:07:17,108
is prohibited.

132
00:07:17,192 --> 00:07:19,650
Further, as a restriction
on higher-level espers,

133
00:07:19,733 --> 00:07:23,025
Misaka is not permitted
to use her electrical abilities.

134
00:07:23,108 --> 00:07:25,025
[RADIO DJ] In other words,
any non-electrical powers

135
00:07:25,108 --> 00:07:27,067
are A-OK for this event!

136
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:28,150
[M STARTER A]
On your marks!

137
00:07:29,692 --> 00:07:31,067
[RADIO DJ]
So, what do you think?

138
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:33,233
Is it fair to say that Tokiwadai
is the favorite to win

139
00:07:33,317 --> 00:07:34,775
this race?

140
00:07:34,858 --> 00:07:36,442
[KUMOKAWA] If they were simply
throwing their abilities around

141
00:07:36,525 --> 00:07:38,567
until the others were
knocked out, maybe.

142
00:07:38,650 --> 00:07:40,525
But given that they
must win a race,

143
00:07:40,608 --> 00:07:42,817
depending on the tactics used,
it's anyone's game.

144
00:07:44,192 --> 00:07:45,525
[KONGO laughs]

145
00:07:45,608 --> 00:07:47,942
As if the other schools
have a chance with their tricks.

146
00:07:48,025 --> 00:07:49,525
Do they know who we are?

147
00:07:49,608 --> 00:07:51,525
They would do well
to respect Tokiwadai's

148
00:07:51,608 --> 00:07:53,525
Gods of Wind and Lightning.

149
00:07:53,608 --> 00:07:56,108
We did spend a lot
of time practicing.

150
00:07:56,192 --> 00:07:58,817
And a lot of time
falling flat on our faces.

151
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:02,400
By the way, did you have
to give us a nickname?

152
00:08:02,483 --> 00:08:04,108
We'll be providing commentary.

153
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:06,108
I'm your Pirate Radio DJ.

154
00:08:06,192 --> 00:08:08,317
I'm your headband-wearing
bare midriff.

155
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,108
[RADIO DJ] And here comes
the starting gun, folks!

156
00:08:11,192 --> 00:08:12,150
[M STARTER A]
Get set!

157
00:08:18,942 --> 00:08:19,900
[BOTH gasp]

158
00:08:19,983 --> 00:08:21,900
Hey! What is this?

159
00:08:21,983 --> 00:08:23,233
[AIRIN GIRL A chuckles]

160
00:08:23,317 --> 00:08:25,942
[RADIO DJ] Oh! Right from
the start! Savage!

161
00:08:26,025 --> 00:08:27,983
Those bandages are
clinging to everyone!

162
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:30,775
Except to the Airin Girl's
High students, of course!

163
00:08:30,858 --> 00:08:31,858
Look at that hustle!

164
00:08:31,942 --> 00:08:33,317
What will happen next?

165
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,692
[KUMOKAWA] According to my
data, she is a telekinetic.

166
00:08:35,775 --> 00:08:39,192
She can control anything
she is in contact with.

167
00:08:39,275 --> 00:08:41,192
Her partner is an esper
who can reduce anything

168
00:08:41,275 --> 00:08:43,108
she touches into raw materials.

169
00:08:43,192 --> 00:08:45,692
It appears she broke down
the track's pavement.

170
00:08:45,775 --> 00:08:46,858
That explains it.

171
00:08:46,942 --> 00:08:48,817
So the black on
the wrappings is asphalt.

172
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:51,817
It's sticky and looks like
it's starting to harden.

173
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,858
It's a smart move when
used right out of the gate.

174
00:08:54,942 --> 00:08:56,150
Why's that?

175
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:58,025
With a few notable exceptions,

176
00:08:58,108 --> 00:09:00,442
most abilities have
a limited range.

177
00:09:00,525 --> 00:09:03,358
Once these girls have run
outside the range of others,

178
00:09:03,442 --> 00:09:05,275
it becomes a normal
race for them.

179
00:09:05,358 --> 00:09:06,733
That makes sense!

180
00:09:06,817 --> 00:09:09,442
But wait, the other teams
are starting to break free.

181
00:09:09,525 --> 00:09:11,900
Crap, my clothes are
heavy and sticky now!

182
00:09:11,983 --> 00:09:13,775
Good luck catching up, losers!

183
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:22,858
[RADIO DJ]
Oh! And what do we have here?

184
00:09:22,942 --> 00:09:23,983
They look like...

185
00:09:24,067 --> 00:09:27,317
[AIRIN GIRL B]
Wait, hamsters? But why?

186
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,525
[KUMOKAWA] It's likely that
Ninoude Affiliated Middle School

187
00:09:29,608 --> 00:09:32,025
set this up before the race.

188
00:09:32,108 --> 00:09:34,317
[KUMOKAWA] Those two are both
rodent-specific telepaths,

189
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,025
if you can believe it.

190
00:09:36,108 --> 00:09:38,275
[RADIO DJ] But are a couple of
hamsters really gonna be enough

191
00:09:38,358 --> 00:09:39,858
to stop them?

192
00:09:39,942 --> 00:09:42,817
[KUMOKAWA] I believe the target
is the band around their ankles.

193
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,192
[RADIO DJ]
So that's it!

194
00:09:44,275 --> 00:09:45,983
