hamsters bite their way

195
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:48,400
through that and
disqualify them!

196
00:09:48,483 --> 00:09:49,983
Not if I can help it!

197
00:09:50,067 --> 00:09:50,817
[AIRIN GIRL B]
Huh?!

198
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:52,608
Where are you going? No!

199
00:09:52,692 --> 00:09:53,942
[KUMOKAWA]
Hmm...

200
00:09:54,025 --> 00:09:55,400
I guess they chewed through
their underwear straps

201
00:09:55,483 --> 00:09:56,483
by mistake.

202
00:09:58,483 --> 00:10:00,150
Hey, come back!

203
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:01,983
[RADIO DJ] They seem too
embarrassed to move!

204
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:03,608
Good job, hamsters!

205
00:10:03,692 --> 00:10:07,358
Approaching the area next are
Habatobi High and Tokiwadai.

206
00:10:07,442 --> 00:10:10,567
And here come
the tiny assassins!

207
00:10:10,650 --> 00:10:12,067
[KUMOKAWA]
Yeah, that's about right.

208
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,483
Hey, jerk!

209
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:16,067
What do you think you're
doing to my darling Kotaro?

210
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:17,400
Shut up!

211
00:10:17,483 --> 00:10:19,692
If you don't like it,
then don't sic 'em on us!

212
00:10:19,775 --> 00:10:20,858
[RADIO DJ]
What's this?

213
00:10:20,942 --> 00:10:23,275
Contestant Misaka
has collapsed as well.

214
00:10:23,358 --> 00:10:26,650
[KUMOKAWA] Her E-M field must
be keeping the hamsters at bay,

215
00:10:26,733 --> 00:10:28,942
and she appears to be
in shock because of it.

216
00:10:31,108 --> 00:10:32,275
How tiresome.

217
00:10:32,358 --> 00:10:34,358
It seems everyone is
pulling out their tricks

218
00:10:34,442 --> 00:10:36,483
and it's devolved
into utter chaos.

219
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:39,400
If it were me there,
I know exactly what I'd do.

220
00:10:39,483 --> 00:10:42,400
I'd control the contestants and
judges with my Mental Out,

221
00:10:42,483 --> 00:10:44,525
and then stroll leisurely
to the finish line

222
00:10:44,608 --> 00:10:46,275
without breaking a sweat.

223
00:10:46,358 --> 00:10:48,567
[KONORI] Well, using it on
people who aren't in the race

224
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:50,525
is against the rules.

225
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:52,233
And so are unrelated items.

226
00:10:56,275 --> 00:10:57,233
[SHOKUHO]
Huh?

227
00:10:59,358 --> 00:11:00,817
[RADIO DJ]
The third event of block seven,

228
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:03,608
the three-legged race,
is entering the home stretch!

229
00:11:03,692 --> 00:11:05,108
Once they round
this last corner,

230
00:11:05,192 --> 00:11:07,233
it's a straight shot
to the finish line!

231
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:10,400
The Habatobi High
team has been bringing

232
00:11:10,483 --> 00:11:12,483
its A-game since breaking free,

233
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:14,483
and is now in the lead
at the final turn!

234
00:11:17,817 --> 00:11:21,025
But Tokiwadai and Ninoude
are still right on their tail!

235
00:11:21,108 --> 00:11:22,233
[NINOUDE GIRL A]
This isn't over.

236
00:11:22,317 --> 00:11:23,858
I know we can get past them!

237
00:11:23,942 --> 00:11:25,942
Yeah? Well you're not
the only ones!

238
00:11:26,025 --> 00:11:27,067
[GROUP yells]

239
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:28,442
[RADIO DJ]
Ahh, what just happened?

240
00:11:28,525 --> 00:11:30,733
Both teams have
inexplicably slipped!

241
00:11:30,817 --> 00:11:32,775
But Tokiwadai avoids
disaster thanks to

242
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:35,067
contestant Misaka's magnetism!

243
00:11:35,150 --> 00:11:37,525
[KUMOKAWA] Habatobi High's
contestant Amime has the ability

244
00:11:37,608 --> 00:11:39,858
to control the frictional
coefficient of anything

245
00:11:39,942 --> 00:11:41,733
he touches.

246
00:11:41,817 --> 00:11:43,358
When we were rounding
the corner,

247
00:11:43,442 --> 00:11:45,525
I leaned into the turn
and touched the track.

248
00:11:45,608 --> 00:11:47,942
It only lasts for a short
time, unfortunately.

249
00:11:48,025 --> 00:11:50,317
[RADIO DJ] Tokiwadai uses the
centrifugal force to close

250
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,775
the gap!

251
00:11:51,858 --> 00:11:54,358
I had a feeling it wasn't
gonna be that easy!

252
00:11:54,442 --> 00:11:55,400
Ready?

253
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,108
[RADIO DJ] Oh! Contestant Amime
has used his ability

254
00:11:59,192 --> 00:12:01,942
so they can skate
their way to the end!

255
00:12:02,025 --> 00:12:04,275
I can collect the moisture
from the air in my hand,

256
00:12:04,358 --> 00:12:06,525
break it down, and ignite it!

257
00:12:06,608 --> 00:12:09,233
And I think it'll make for
a fine rocket boost here!

258
00:12:09,317 --> 00:12:10,733
It's a straight shot
to the goal.

259
00:12:10,817 --> 00:12:12,192
We got this in the bag!

260
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:16,650
[BOTH yell]

261
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:19,733
[RADIO DJ] Uh-oh!
Habatobi High has lost control!

262
00:12:19,817 --> 00:12:22,067
They're heading out of bounds!

263
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:25,858
[AMIME]
Oh, no!

264
00:12:27,525 --> 00:12:28,983
[AMIME, TODOROKI grunt]

265
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:30,067
[RADIO DJ]
What's this?

266
00:12:30,150 --> 00:12:31,900
A gym mat has
flown through the air,

267
00:12:31,983 --> 00:12:33,858
catching the team
before the crash landing!

268
00:12:35,942 --> 00:12:37,817
What team but Tokiwadai
could have performed

269
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:39,650
such a dramatic rescue?

270
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:41,525
Contestant Misaka
pulled up the safety mat

271
00:12:41,608 --> 00:12:44,108
with her magnetism, and
Contestant Kongo launched it

272
00:12:44,192 --> 00:12:46,692
toward them with her Aero Hand!

273
00:12:46,775 --> 00:12:49,525
One false move and that could
have gone all sorts of wrong!

274
00:12:49,608 --> 00:12:52,358
But that combo was
performed flawlessly!

275
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:54,900
Damn it!

276
00:12:54,983 --> 00:12:57,317
If we hadn't screwed that up,
we would have won!

277
00:12:58,817 --> 00:12:59,733
Hang on.

278
00:12:59,817 --> 00:13:01,567
[AMIME]
What?

279
00:13:01,650 --> 00:13:03,150
[TODOROKI]
Iron filings?

280
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:05,317
[MIKOTO] Back from when we were
wrapped up in those bandages,

281
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:07,858
I used the opportunity to
mix iron into the asphalt

282
00:13:07,942 --> 00:13:09,692
before it hardened.

283
00:13:09,775 --> 00:13:11,775
I was planning to intervene
if I saw you approaching

284
00:13:11,858 --> 00:13:13,733
the finish line before us.

285
00:13:13,817 --> 00:13:16,025
But you guys kinda
saved me the trouble.

286
00:13:16,108 --> 00:13:17,483
Sorry for being so sneaky!

287
00:13:19,108 --> 00:13:20,733
She didn't miss a beat.

288
00:13:20,817 --> 00:13:22,900
What do they teach them
at that fancy school?

289
00:13:22,983 --> 00:13:25,317
[TODOROKI] She basically just
told us no matter what we did,

290
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,317
we were gonna lose.

291
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:30,483
[RADIO DJ] And finally, the
Tokiwadai team crosses

292
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:33,358
the finish line!

293
00:13:33,442 --> 00:13:35,567
[KUMOKAWA] It's not the
most surprising result.

294
00:13:35,650 --> 00:13:36,900
Perhaps the other schools
would have stood

295
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:39,650
a better chance if they
teamed up on them.

296
00:13:39,733 --> 00:13:41,525
Hey! They won!

297
00:13:41,608 --> 00:13:43,817
[UIHARU] They make a
pretty good pair, after all.

298
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:45,358
If it weren't for my injuries.

299
00:13:45,442 --> 00:13:46,942
I would be the one
standing next to her,

300
00:13:47,025 --> 00:13:49,108
basking in the glory
of our teamwork!

301
00:13:49,192 --> 00:13:52,400
[squeals] Mitsuko Kongo!
Get outta the way!

302
00:13:52,483 --> 00:13:54,192
You're blocking
my view of Sissy!

303
00:13:54,275 --> 00:13:56,525
[XOCHITL] Damn it. How do I
answer a call on this thing?

304
00:13:56,608 --> 00:13:57,817
Is it a new model?

305
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:00,108
I wish they hadn't given
me this crazy phone.

306
00:14:00,192 --> 00:14:02,650
I wouldn't be having this
problem with a regular cell.

307
00:14:05,150 --> 00:14:06,483
[SATEN] If you pull that part
on the side out,

308
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:08,025
you'll be able to
use the screen,

309
00:14:08,108 --> 00:14:10,067
and then you can call them
back from your call history.

310
00:14:11,525 --> 00:14:13,025
Oh, you're right.

311
00:14:13,108 --> 00:14:14,900
Thanks, that was very helpf--

312
00:14:14,983 --> 00:14:15,942
[yells]

313
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,775
Did I do something wrong?

314
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:21,858
Uh... No. I just...

315
00:14:21,942 --> 00:14:24,317
[UIHARU]
Hey, Saten, we're leaving!

316
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,567
Oh. Mm-hmm! Be right there!

317
00:14:33,192 --> 00:14:35,025
Um... Need something?

318
00:14:35,108 --> 00:14:36,650
You seem awfully familiar.

319
00:14:36,733 --> 00:14:38,650
Have we met somewhere before?

320
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:40,942
No. You must be imagining it.

321
00:14:44,358 --> 00:14:46,275
Heh. Yeah, I guess so!

322
00:14:46,358 --> 00:14:47,733
[UIHARU]
Hey, Saten!

323
00:14:47,817 --> 00:14:50,025
Right. Coming!

324
00:14:54,192 --> 00:14:57,025
[phone ringing]

325
00:14:58,942 --> 00:15:00,567
[MEMBER DOCTOR]
Why didn't you answer before?

326
00:15:00,650 --> 00:15:02,150
Are you in trouble?

327
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,942
[XOCHITL] No. I just couldn't
get on the phone quick enough.

328
00:15:05,025 --> 00:15:08,108
[DOCTOR] You've safely managed
to get into Academy City, then?

329
00:15:08,192 --> 00:15:09,442
I have.

330
00:15:09,525 --> 00:15:10,942
[DOCTOR] This is your first
mission for MEMBER,

331
00:15:11,025 --> 00:15:12,608
so you'd better succeed.

332
00:15:12,692 --> 00:15:14,233
You need to make
a good impression,

333
00:15:14,317 --> 00:15:16,400
my young lady of the Aztec.

334
00:15:16,483 --> 00:15:18,150
I know.

335
00:15:18,233 --> 00:15:21,400
[RADIO DJ] Oh! Nagatenjouki
Academy breaks ahead of the pack

336
00:15:21,483 --> 00:15:24,483
and is the first across
the finish line!

337
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:25,858
They're on fire!

338
00:15:25,942 --> 00:15:27,483
[MISAKA SISTER A]
The Daihasei Festival.

339
00:15:27,567 --> 00:15:30,900
Misaka does not currently
receive any formal education,

340
00:15:30,983 --> 00:15:33,150
so she cannot participate.

341
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:34,192
[CAT meows]

342
00:15:35,358 --> 00:15:37,983
[MISAKA SISTER A]
Let's go back to the hospital.

343
00:15:38,067 --> 00:15:39,025
[SATEN]
Misaka!

344
00:15:40,775 --> 00:15:42,983
We watched you in
the three-legged race!

345
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:44,442
Impressive as always.

346
00:15:44,525 --> 00:15:45,983
[MIKOTO chuckles]

347
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:48,692
I'm glad we won, but we did get
pretty dirty in the process.

348
00:15:48,775 --> 00:15:50,525
Hey, whatever,
a win's a win, right?

349
00:15:50,608 --> 00:15:52,942
And man, I was surprised
by how fast you were!

350
00:15:53,025 --> 00:15:54,775
Those were boys
in the same year as us,

351
00:15:54,858 --> 00:15:56,192
but you passed them, no problem!

352
00:15:56,275 --> 00:15:58,358
[chuckles]
Thanks, I guess.

353
00:15:58,442 --> 00:16:00,150
Ever since I was little,
I've been pretty qui--

354
00:16:00,233 --> 00:16:02,358
[MISUZU] Mikoto has been a
little speed demon ever since

355
00:16:02,442 --> 00:16:04,192
she was in kindergarten.

356
00:16:04,275 --> 00:16:05,858
[MIKOTO]
Oh, Mama!

357
00:16:05,942 --> 00:16:06,858
Yoo-hoo!

358
00:16:06,942 --> 00:16:07,858
[MIKOTO]
What's up?

359
00:16:07,942 --> 00:16:09,108
I thought we were
meeting later--

360
00:16:09,192 --> 00:16:10,567
[UIHARU, SATEN]
Mama?!

361
00:16:10,650 --> 00:16:13,733
Uh... "Mama" is what I
used to call her as a kid,

362
00:16:13,817 --> 00:16:15,317
so it kinda slipped out.

363
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,192
It's not like I do
that all the time.

364
00:16:17,275 --> 00:16:19,567
[SATEN] Wait, Mama as in her
mother? I didn't mishear that?

365
00:16:19,650 --> 00:16:21,483
Not her older sister,
but her mother?

366
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:23,442
You look like you're
barely 20 years old!

367
00:16:23,525 --> 00:16:24,983
Oh. Yeah, that.

368
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:27,817
[MISUZU] Ah... I take it you
two are Mikoto's friends?

369
00:16:27,900 --> 00:16:30,233
What a kind thing
for you to say.

370
00:16:30,317 --> 00:16:32,275
[SATEN] Ah, but you know,
now that I'm really taking

371
00:16:32,358 --> 00:16:35,775
a good look, I can totally see
parts of Misaka in you.

372
00:16:35,858 --> 00:16:37,233
Chest excluded.

373
00:16:37,317 --> 00:16:38,525
Hey, uh, Saten?

374
00:16:38,608 --> 00:16:40,733
Why don't you and I
have a little chat later?

375
00:16:40,817 --> 00:16:42,483
Just the two of us.

376
00:16:42,567 --> 00:16:45,275
[SATEN] I'm kidding!
It was just a joke, okay?

377
00:16:45,358 --> 00:16:46,692
[MIKOTO]
Sure.

378
00:16:46,775 --> 00:16:48,817
Oh. Hey, where's Kuroko?

379
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:52,067
She was going out on Judgment
patrol last time I heard.

380
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:54,650
If you need her for something,
I can call her.

381
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:56,650
Thanks, but it's fine.

382
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:58,483
I was just thinking I
could ask her if she would

383
00:16:58,567 --> 00:17:00,650
teleport me back to
Tokiwadai so I could change

384
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:03,067
out of this filthy
uniform I'm stuck in.

385
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:04,567
Right.

386
00:17:04,650 --> 00:17:06,942
I can see why you wouldn't
want to keep that on anymore.

387
00:17:07,025 --> 00:17:08,942
But looking at the time,

388
00:17:09,025 --> 00:17:12,358
I don't think I can make it back
before the next race starts.

389
00:17:12,442 --> 00:17:14,150
You could always ask
someone to fill in for you

390
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:15,275
in the meantime.

391
00:17:15,358 --> 00:17:16,442
It wouldn't be long.

392
00:17:16,525 --> 00:17:17,817
Yeah, maybe.

393
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,983
That idiot and I have
our showdown though,

394
00:17:20,067 --> 00:17:21,567
so I gotta make sure
I'm there for that.

395
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:23,442
And who might "that idiot" be?

396
00:17:23,525 --> 00:17:25,650
Mama is curious!

397
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:27,525
Why are you making
such a big deal about it?

398
00:17:27,608 --> 00:17:29,025
There's nothing
special about him.

399
00:17:29,108 --> 00:17:30,733
He's just some stupid guy.

400
00:17:30,817 --> 00:17:32,525
Who? Tell me!

401
00:17:32,608 --> 00:17:34,150
[SATEN] From what I've
gathered, he's someone who

402
00:17:34,233 --> 00:17:36,733
Misaka apparently owes a lot to.

403
00:17:36,817 --> 00:17:38,442
[MISUZU]
Ooh, tell me more.

404
00:17:38,525 --> 00:17:39,817
[UIHARU]
Hey! I just remembered!

405
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:42,108
I was watching the scavenger
hunt coverage earlier,

406
00:17:42,192 --> 00:17:44,900
and I saw Misaka
with a spiky-haired boy.

407
00:17:44,983 --> 00:17:46,108
[MISUZU]
Spiky-haired?

408
00:17:46,192 --> 00:17:47,650
Oh! That boy!

409
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,108
[SATEN]
Wait, you know who he is?

410
00:17:49,192 --> 00:17:50,900
[MISUZU] Yeah, I happened
to see them this morning.

411
00:17:50,983 --> 00:17:53,442
Misaka was with what looked
like a high-school aged boy,

412
00:17:53,525 --> 00:17:54,608
and said that if he beat her,

413
00:17:54,692 --> 00:17:56,650
she'd do anything
he said, or something.

414
00:17:56,733 --> 00:17:57,775
[MIKOTO]
Come on!

415
00:17:57,858 --> 00:18:01,275
There are three of them
against me now?

416
00:18:01,358 --> 00:18:03,942
[M STUDENTS yelling]

417
00:18:06,942 --> 00:18:10,775
[AWATSUKI] Wow. They're
being incredibly forceful.

418
00:18:10,858 --> 00:18:12,275
It's almost kind of gruesome.

419
00:18:19,775 --> 00:18:21,150
Awatsuki.

420
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,233
[AWATSUKI]
Yes?

421
00:18:22,317 --> 00:18:24,108
Have you ever been
in a fight before?

422
00:18:24,192 --> 00:18:25,150
A fight?

423
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,650
[WANNAI] I mean, besides
that time against STUDY.

424
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:32,942
We've been taught all this time
that the enemy is within us,

425
00:18:33,025 --> 00:18:34,942
that we're training not
to be better than others,

426
00:18:35,025 --> 00:18:37,483
but to overcome
our own weaknesses.

427
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:39,900
But looking at kids
from the other schools,

428
00:18:39,983 --> 00:18:42,150
I can't help but wonder
if our competitive sides

429
00:18:42,233 --> 00:18:44,817
aren't somewhat lacking.

430
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:46,108
You might be right.

431
00:18:46,192 --> 00:18:47,650
I don't know if we'd
be able to muster up

432
00:18:47,733 --> 00:18:50,108
that kind of force and power
in the pursuit of victory

433
00:18:50,192 --> 00:18:51,942
like they do.

434
00:18:52,025 --> 00:18:54,108
[WANNAI] And I do believe
what we've been taught.

435
00:18:54,192 --> 00:18:57,567
I don't think it's right to hurt
others or look down on them.

436
00:18:57,650 --> 00:18:59,108
But...

437
00:18:59,192 --> 00:19:01,442
I wonder if we shouldn't learn
how to fight competitively.

438
00:19:01,525 --> 00:19:03,358
Just in case.

439
00:19:03,442 --> 00:19:04,692
Honestly...

440
00:19:04,775 --> 00:19:07,858
I've never gotten angry,
not even in the one fight.

441
00:19:07,942 --> 00:19:10,442
So that's why you asked
me about that earlier.

442
00:19:10,525 --> 00:19:12,983
--Well, I'm in the same boat.
--[WANNAI] I've got it!

443
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:14,192
Hey, Awatsuki.

444
00:19:14,275 --> 00:19:15,650
Would you mind trying
to get angry with me

445
00:19:15,733 --> 00:19:16,858
so we can practice?

446
00:19:16,942 --> 00:19:17,900
[AWATSUKI]
Huh?!

447
00:19:19,775 --> 00:19:22,400
Um... Okay.

448
00:19:22,483 --> 00:19:24,775
You... You, uh...

449
00:19:24,858 --> 00:19:26,067
...suck!

450
00:19:27,775 --> 00:19:30,275
[STUDENTS] Down with
Tokiwadai Middle School!

451
00:19:30,358 --> 00:19:31,900
[M HOSTILE A]
Elite school? Yeah, right!

452
00:19:31,983 --> 00:19:34,233
They're all girls,
and middle schoolers, at that!

453
00:19:34,317 --> 00:19:36,025
We can't let ourselves
lose to them!

454
00:19:36,108 --> 00:19:37,358
[STUDENTS]
Yeah!

455
00:19:37,442 --> 00:19:39,025
[KONGO]
Oh, goodness.

456
00:19:39,108 --> 00:19:41,275
I'm glad you have
so much spirit.

457
00:19:41,358 --> 00:19:43,067
After all, every school
should be trying to win

458
00:19:43,150 --> 00:19:44,442
this competition.

459
00:19:44,525 --> 00:19:46,567
However, we are one of
the five who actually have

460
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:48,192
a shot at taking the title.

461
00:19:48,275 --> 00:19:50,358
We are not going to roll over
and lose just because

462
00:19:50,442 --> 00:19:52,025
you wish us to.

463
00:19:52,108 --> 00:19:55,150
Tokiwadai will beat you
so badly that you'll be telling

464
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:57,733
your grandchildren
how fearsome we are.

465
00:19:57,817 --> 00:19:59,900
Look at Kongo,
talking a big game!

466
00:19:59,983 --> 00:20:02,942
Such poise in the face
of such furious opposition!

467
00:20:03,025 --> 00:20:04,150
Very impressive!

468
00:20:04,233 --> 00:20:06,442
Let's show them what
a real cheer looks like.

469
00:20:06,525 --> 00:20:08,275
Tokiwadai... go!

470
00:20:08,358 --> 00:20:09,900
Go.

471
00:20:09,983 --> 00:20:12,025
Oh, please, we can do
better than that!

472
00:20:12,108 --> 00:20:12,900
Once more!

473
00:20:12,983 --> 00:20:14,067
Go!

474
00:20:14,150 --> 00:20:16,400
--[KONGO] Once more!
--[GROUP] Go!

475
00:20:16,483 --> 00:20:17,733
[F TOKIWADAI C]
This is unfortunate.

476
00:20:17,817 --> 00:20:19,442
What are we going to do?

477
00:20:19,525 --> 00:20:20,608
[WANNAI]
Is there a problem?

478
00:20:21,942 --> 00:20:22,858
Well, yes.

479
00:20:22,942 --> 00:20:24,442
The next contest
is about to start,

480
00:20:24,525 --> 00:20:26,775
but Misaka is nowhere
to be found.

481
00:20:26,858 --> 00:20:27,817
[WANNAI]
Oh.

482
00:20:30,317 --> 00:20:32,733
[MISAKA SISTER A] "Once again,
Misaka finds herself watching

483
00:20:32,817 --> 00:20:33,983
the games.

484
00:20:34,067 --> 00:20:36,192
But it is not as if she
is depressed about being

485
00:20:36,275 --> 00:20:38,775
unable to compete,
you understand. Yeah,"

486
00:20:38,858 --> 00:20:41,817
says Misaka, at odds
with her emotions.

487
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,317
[CAT meows]

488
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,567
Although she cannot deny
that there is some feeling

489
00:20:45,650 --> 00:20:47,358
of alienation.

490
00:20:47,442 --> 00:20:49,608
There! Hey, Misaka!

491
00:20:49,692 --> 00:20:50,567
[MISAKA SISTER A]
Yes?

492
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:51,733
[WANNAI]
Huh?

493
00:20:51,817 --> 00:20:53,317
Why aren't you wearing
your gym uniform?

494
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,442
We're all supposed to be.

495
00:20:55,525 --> 00:20:56,650
[AWATSUKI]
Oh, I bet I know.

496
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:58,733
I saw the three-legged
race earlier.

497
00:20:58,817 --> 00:21:01,067
You took it off because those
other girls got it all dirty,

498
00:21:01,150 --> 00:21:02,483
didn't you?

499
00:21:02,567 --> 00:21:04,817
Oh, yeah, and you have
nothing else to change into!

500
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,650
In that case,
you can borrow mine.

501
00:21:10,733 --> 00:21:11,858
[MIKOTO]
Oh, man!

502
00:21:11,942 --> 00:21:13,192
I thought if I used my ability,

503
00:21:13,275 --> 00:21:14,692
I could get there
and back in time,

504
00:21:14,775 --> 00:21:15,983
but this is pushing it!

505
00:21:19,233 --> 00:21:21,317
Hey, everyone,
sorry I'm late! I--

506
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:23,275
It's not too small
on you, is it?

507
00:21:23,358 --> 00:21:25,608
It shouldn't obstruct
any movement.

508
00:21:25,692 --> 00:21:28,192
In fact, it's quite loose
across the chest.

509
00:21:28,275 --> 00:21:30,483
I'll take care of the little one
while you're out there.

510
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:32,817
Huh?

511
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,483
[WANNAI]
Is something wrong?

512
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:37,192
No, I just thought I saw
someone for a second.

513
00:21:37,275 --> 00:21:40,692
[MIKOTO groans]
What in the world is she doing?

514
00:21:40,775 --> 00:21:43,442
[KOZAKU] So?
How is everything coming along?

515
00:21:43,525 --> 00:21:45,067
In place and at the ready.

516
00:21:45,150 --> 00:21:47,150
There shouldn't be
any problems at all.

517
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:48,525
Just like you wanted.

518
00:21:48,608 --> 00:21:51,025
This is going to render her
completely powerless.

519
00:21:51,108 --> 00:21:52,858
[M HOSTILE B]
Baba, we're getting started.

520
00:21:52,942 --> 00:21:55,108
Oh, my bad! On my way!

521
00:21:55,192 --> 00:21:58,442
Well, well, he sounds
confident, doesn't he?

522
00:21:58,525 --> 00:22:00,608
I guess I should expect
as much from MEMBER,

523
00:22:00,692 --> 00:22:04,650
the dark side outfit directly
under the governing board.

524
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:06,358
But I'll reserve judgment
until I see what

525
00:22:06,442 --> 00:22:08,150
he's actually capable of.

526
00:22:25,942 --> 00:22:27,150
[BABA laughs]

527
00:23:58,192 --> 00:23:59,317
[MISAKA SISTER A]
"Oh, dear.

528
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:01,067
Misaka has been mistaken
for her big sister,

529
00:24:01,150 --> 00:24:03,067
and ends up having
to compete in the games.

530
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:04,900
She must do her best
for the others,"

531
00:24:04,983 --> 00:24:07,483
enthuses Misaka, in the style
of an animated program's

532
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:08,858
preview segment.

533
00:24:08,942 --> 00:24:11,567
[MIKOTO] Uh, well. At least
you sound determined.

